<DOC><DOCNO> AP880926-0121 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-26-88 1512EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-BRF--CathedralBurglary     09-26 0183</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Cathedral Burglary,0187</SECOND><HEAD>Burglary At St. Patrick's Cathedral</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A burglar who may have spent the night hiding inlocked St. Patrick's Cathedral stole cash from a collection box andescaped before dawn Monday, one week after a killing in thelandmark church, police said.   Capt. Barry Noxon said two janitors saw the man breaking intothe box at about 4 a.m. They did not see him leave but police wereunable to find him, Noxon said.   The doors were locked at the time of the burglary and Noxon saiddetectives suspect the man stayed inside since Sunday.   Noxon said ``it doesn't appear he got away with very much.''   Cardinal John J. O'Connor, who lives in the attached rectory,was assigned around-the-clock police protection last week after aderanged naked man killed an usher in the cathedral. The assailantwas killed by a police bullet.   In February 1987, two men ransacked O'Connor's bedroom andprivate office while he was out of town. Two armed men stole $7,000from cathedral ushers on Nov. 30, 1985, said archdiocese spokesmanJoseph Zwilling.</TEXT></DOC>